		<div id="post_message_1237767">
                  
                  Well, to make it all more difficult, I would have to agree with Emi on the fact that if a &quot;Shield&quot; is implimented it will come at the cost of DPS.  Just being in procimity of a Sorc, does not mean that anyone should have &quot;Shielding&quot; form incoming spells.<br />
A Sorc should still have to put forth effort to &quot;Shield&quot; the ones near them from incoming spells, and that is going to come at the cost that they most stop their DPS to accomidate those that need protection.  At least not automaticly.  Make it a proc chance, yeah then I would agree, because that leaves that the Sorc must do something to make the &quot;Shielding&quot; happen.  Or are we speaking of leaving it a spell that the Sorc still must cast, then I would agree.  But if we are talking about a aura or dance or song, then no.  I would rather see us focus on the DPS side of things.
                  
		</div>
