See, my logic is that it would work like this:<br />
<br />
Some spells can definatly be countered or nullified / reduced from our wards, but for this &quot;long reuse, devistating effect&quot; aoes, you know, the raid wipers, thats where our sanctuaries would truely come into play.<br />
<br />
I hope they implement like a 5 second cast AOE that is uninteruptable that would deal devistating damage (hint, almost always fatal) to anyone in range, they would require people to either flee quickly out of range, OR for the sorcerer to drop the appriopriate Sanctuary and people can take cover while still doing their dps.<br />
<br />
If you think of it in these terms, the sorcerer just added a lot of DPS potiential to the raid and made it much safer, as people can just run with in range of the sanctuary and continue to beat on the foe.<br />
<br />
Then, if they added some offensive benefit to people with in the radious for a breif time, that would give us even more offensive &quot;extras&quot; to bring to the raid. Seeing as these would be on a longer-ish reuse timers, they would NOT be factored into our dps equation in any shape or form, merely a nice little temporary bonus if you will.<br />
<br />
But, that is just purely a &quot;if they wanted to&quot; factor, the aoe prevention is the real important part!
                  
