<br />
I do see your conserns, but if it is only for 15 seconds, i doubt it would cause too much of a hellacious lag. If it did, then they could fix it to a instant + every 2 second application or something simular to lower the server load while still making it get most people.<br />
<br />
If they implemented the &quot;super aoes&quot; like i desribed which are highly televised to people with good spell identification (hint, another thing sorcerers would be good for in a raid!) then we know that we have 5 or 6 seconds to cast that instant cast Sanctuary so our allies can take cover.<br />
<br />
If it pulses ever 2 seconds + initial cast, then we would hit most people on the initial (the effect would last for 6 seconds on the person, so they have some leeway if they get out of range briefly) and in most cases they would still have 2-4 seconds to &quot;hop in&quot; the radious if they were not in the initial cast.<br />
<br />
<br />
This would hopefully satisfy issues with lag while still allowing people to &quot;take shelter&quot; instead of &quot;missing the shield.&quot;
                  
